<%
	#@email_configs = Array.new
	reply_email  = "support@yourcompany.com" 
	to_email 	 = "support@yourcompany.freshdesk.com" 
	to_email 	 = @email_configs.first.to_email unless @email_configs.first.nil?
	reply_email  = @email_configs.first.reply_email unless @email_configs.first.nil?
%>
<div class="sidepanel wordwrap">
		<h3 class="title">Email Settings</h3> 
		<p>Your users send support emails to <strong><%=reply_email%></strong></p>
		<p>You must forward your support emails to your unique email address <strong><%=to_email%></strong>. Freshdesk will fetch those emails and convert them as tickets.</p>
		<p>You can add multiple email addresses if you support multiple products - each having its own support email address.</p>
		
		<h3 class="title">Reply Emails from Freshdesk</h3> 
		
		<p>Reply emails from Freshdesk will automatically use your original support email ids as the From email address.</p>
		<p>While most of your emails will be delivered, to be on the safer side you must create an <a target="_blank" title="Learn more about creating SPF records" href="http://support.freshdesk.com/solution/categories/4/folders/7/articles/5-spf-record">SPF record</a> in your DNS zone file if you are using emails in your own domain. This helps in ensuring proper delivery of email.</p> 
		
		<a target="_blank" href="http://support.freshdesk.com/solution/categories/4/folders/7/articles/2-converting-your-support-email-into-freshdesk-tickets">Read our Email Settings article for more information...</a>
